The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Monday, January 06, 2003 				 Nepal talks
																								Kathmandu, Jan. 5 (afp): The Nepalese government has asked a mediation committee to offer peace talks with Maoist rebels, mediators said today.																								The Nepalese government had written to the committee to convey a message to the rebels to come and sit down for the talks, said a member of the committee for peace dialogue facilitation.
